Package com.shouldis.bitset

Interface WordBiFunction

public interface WordBiFunction
Functional interface used in conjunction with BitSet.apply(int, WordBiFunction, long). apply(long, long) should represent a function used to manipulate the bits within the words of a BitSet.
Author:
Aaron Shouldis

  • Method Details

    • apply

      long apply​(long word, long mask)
      Function used to perform operations on the words within a BitSet.
      Parameters:
      word - the original word to manipulate.
      mask - the second word typically used as a mask in WordBiFunctions.
      Returns:
      the manipulated word.

    • combine

      static WordBiFunction combine​(WordBiFunction first, WordBiFunction second)
      Creates a WordBiFunction which performs the two specified WordFunctions first and second in sequence.
      Parameters:
      first - the first WordBiFunction to be applied to the arguments.
      second - the second WordBiFunction to be applied to the result of first.
      Returns:
      a WordBiFunction which applies both first and second.
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if first or second are null.
